<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="269" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="8.[104,1315,290,683]" pageId="8" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[107,478,451,480]" pageId="8" pageNumber="269">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix II. Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. Relative to many other treeshrew species, the Splendid Treeshrew is quite rare and has a decreasing population trend. It is threatened by forest destruction, particularly in Kalimantan, and is not known to occur in any protected areas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
